The paper focuses on building resource-efficient models for intent detection in conversational systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of pretrained models and their effectiveness, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions hyperparameter tuning, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset for intent detection, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
